Dialogue: 0,0:00:47.23,0:00:47.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Pardon me?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:49.65,0:00:51.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What do you think yer doin', you?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:55.78,0:00:58.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So... You're gonna keep following me around?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:58.70,0:01:01.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's not that I don't want to leave. I just don't know how.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:01.66,0:01:06.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I might learn how to leave once I regain all of my memories.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:06.62,0:01:09.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And just how are your memories gonna return?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:09.96,0:01:12.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,By gathering all of the Numbers.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:12.67,0:01:14.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Numbers?!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:14.13,0:01:17.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're not about to tell me that I'm the\N one who's gotta do it, are you?!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:17.84,0:01:20.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yuma's over there talking to himself again...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:20.97,0:01:24.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I wonder if this "Duelist Spirit" of his really exists...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:24.56,0:01:27.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's a definite, {\i1}definite{\i0} "no", pal!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:27.52,0:01:29.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So quit following me!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:29.02,0:01:32.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yuma... You're becoming really weird lately...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:32.90,0:01:35.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Observation number two...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:35.19,0:01:36.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"You are weird."
Dialogue: 0,0:01:36.65,0:01:37.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll be sure to remember that.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:37.78,0:01:39.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I am {\i1}not{\i0} weird!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:41.07,0:01:42.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wh-What the?!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:44.58,0:01:46.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's wrong, Sis?!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:46.00,0:01:47.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's gone...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:47.66,0:01:49.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The manuscript's gone...!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:49.17,0:01:50.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The system's been infected by a virus...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:50.96,0:01:53.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And there's only one hour until the deadline...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:53.92,0:01:55.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,C-Calm down, Sis...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:55.92,0:01:58.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I won't make the delivery...!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:58.38,0:02:00.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,At times like this, my sister gets...!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.68,0:02:02.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We better get outta here...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.35,0:02:03.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Right...!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.85,0:02:04.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yuma!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:04.68,0:02:08.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You better find an explanation for this pronto!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.10,0:02:13.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's impossible to deal with my sister when she gets like that...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.27,0:02:16.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That aside, this delay is way too much.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:16.99,0:02:17.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.86,0:02:20.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The traffic lights are all corrupted.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.57,0:02:22.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And the monorail's stuck in its tracks.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:22.32,0:02:23.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wh-What's this?!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.87,0:02:24.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Whoa!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.58,0:02:26.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How lucky!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.08,0:02:27.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's raining juice!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.79,0:02:29.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,H-Hey, Yuma!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.54,0:02:31.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You can't just take those!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.67,0:02:33.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll give 'em bac-
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.13,0:02:37.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Cleaning! Cleaning!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.50,0:02:36.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Hey, you! Lem'me go!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.46,0:02:37.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Lay off!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.46,0:02:41.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Today, the city suffered a massive system downage.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.09,0:02:41.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The cause-
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.43,0:02:43.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The manuscript's gone...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.72,0:02:45.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Time to dig in!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.01,0:02:46.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I missed the delivery!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.85,0:02:50.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Earlier today, I got grabbed by one of those O-Bots!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.56,0:02:52.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My, my, as did I!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.02,0:02:54.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? What's with that?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.02,0:02:56.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It was just on the news!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.02,0:02:58.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's a big crisis!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.07,0:03:00.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The public vending machine broke down.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.36,0:03:01.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wow, the monorail's moving again.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.99,0:03:04.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Looks like things are finally working again.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.95,0:03:08.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So basically, I wasn't the only one who lost all their data?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.91,0:03:09.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sis?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.87,0:03:11.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Something smells fishy.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.37,0:03:12.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- Huh?\N - Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.63,0:03:15.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,NO!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.92,0:03:17.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I meant this {\i1}incident{\i0} smells!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.75,0:03:19.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can't waste any time!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.26,0:03:20.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Gotta replenish my energy!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.47,0:03:22.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's mine!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.30,0:03:23.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Gotta hurry and eat!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.97,0:03:27.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,God!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.85,0:03:33.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So this is the method humans use to replenish their energy?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.02,0:03:34.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.77,0:03:36.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That energy...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.94,0:03:39.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...is then released after said replenishment...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.94,0:03:40.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...I think?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.70,0:03:44.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There's lots of reasons for this!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.53,0:03:47.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I am confused as to why I can't join you inside there.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.66,0:03:48.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Idiot!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.58,0:03:50.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's obvious, ain't it?!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.00,0:03:52.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's a {\i1}trade secret{\i0} method we use to release our energy!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.04,0:03:54.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If someone happened to see us while doing it, we'd {\i1}die!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.50,0:03:55.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My word!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.75,0:03:58.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,To think you would go to such lengths for nourishment...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.84,0:04:00.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Observation number three...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.92,0:04:04.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Humans must eat and release in an endless combination.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.13,0:04:07.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,However, they will die the moment anyone sees them doing this."
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.51,0:04:08.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Can it!!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.97,0:04:10.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But it is peculiar.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.93,0:04:13.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If humans really operate in such a perfect combination...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.69,0:04:18.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...why is your Dueling so incompetent?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.40,0:04:21.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And what the heck is {\i1}that{\i0} supposed to mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.36,0:04:24.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Put bluntly, you are unskilled when it comes to Dueling.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.99,0:04:25.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Shut {\i1}up!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.53,0:04:28.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There's no such {\i1}thing{\i0} as a "perfect human"!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.70,0:04:30.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's more {\i1}fun{\i0} when you fail!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.83,0:04:34.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If you fail, you will lose something of great value.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.83,0:04:36.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Humph!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.83,0:04:39.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can't bring it to 'em if I'm scared of failing!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.75,0:04:43.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A spirit like you will never get it!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.10,0:04:55.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I'm sure that I have a very important mission to fulfill.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.19,0:05:00.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I'm certain that I have been trapped with Yuma in order to see that said mission is completed.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.57,0:05:04.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Despite that, my memories have been trapped within 99 different cards...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.99,0:05:07.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}And then scatterd bearing the name "Numbers".
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.61,0:05:11.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}My memories won't return unless I gather these Numbers...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.66,0:05:16.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Numbers seem to have the power to control humans...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.87,0:05:23.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Right... This young boy was able to use the Numbers to its fullest while I couldn't...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.13,0:05:25.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Why...?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.01,0:05:28.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Is it because he secretly harbors something within...?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.40,0:05:41.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What is this place?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.60,0:06:03.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Whether it's rainy, or windy,\N or a cold winter blizzard, or the burning sun,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.74,0:06:06.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}they're all ingredients to color each day. \NDon't lose heart, will or love.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.84,0:06:09.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The kindness you gave me was strict,\N when we clashed I learned irritation.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.91,0:06:13.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}It starts by recognizing our differences, dancing freely,\N the creation of Heaven and Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.25,0:06:21.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The truth is, I was lonely. Until I met you.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.32,0:06:27.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I lied to myself that being alone was easier.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.10,0:06:34.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}My favorite books and hobbies,\N they don't seem to match.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.50,0:06:38.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}You were the only one to nod in agreement with me.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.71,0:06:41.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Happiness and sadness and anger and\N Do and Re and Mi and Fa and So and La and Ti and Do,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.51,0:06:43.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}It doesn't work unless they're different,\N the harmony and the scenario.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.25,0:06:47.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}No one is exactly the same,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.55,0:06:51.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}because that's the reason for living.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.59,0:06:56.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Even if the sounds are dissonant from time to time,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.02,0:07:02.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}don't give up on the strength that will get you through.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.26,0:07:06.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}When we reach the edge of the world,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.33,0:07:10.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}the view we see will be the truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.40,0:07:13.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Whether it's rainy, or windy,\N or a cold winter blizzard, or the burning sun,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.31,0:07:16.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}They're all ingredients to color each day.\N Don't lose heart, will or love.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.41,0:07:19.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}the kindness you gave me was strict,\N when we clashed I learned irritation.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.48,0:07:23.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}It starts by recognizing our differences, dancing freely,\N the creation of Heaven and Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.40,0:07:42.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,OW!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.24,0:07:47.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(414,502)}"Numbers 3:\N A Sudden Incident During the Aftermath!!"
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.71,0:07:47.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Su-weet! The guy's not here anymore!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.29,0:07:50.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,O-Oh, snap!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.74,0:07:54.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'M LATE!!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.84,0:07:56.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Made it on time~
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.80,0:07:59.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay! Listen up, everyone!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.38,0:08:04.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Due to yesterday's communication error, the entire school's broadcasting computers are currently down as a result.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.72,0:08:06.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So we can't access the textbooks.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.60,0:08:08.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The cause of the error was-
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.06,0:08:11.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Me! Please let me answer this!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.35,0:08:14.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh? Committee Chairman, you know something about this?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.86,0:08:19.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I do! I simply used my programming skills to mentally place myself in a similar setting.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.28,0:08:25.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,To summarize, the malfunctioning issue was caused by someone infiltrating the city's host computer.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.41,0:08:27.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So if I were to create-
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.74,0:08:28.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sensei!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.37,0:08:30.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How 'bout we make today into a Duel tournament!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.87,0:08:33.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hmm... Perhaps.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.58,0:08:35.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why not?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.38,0:08:36.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Booyah!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.92,0:08:39.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm gonna bring it to every last one of you today!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.30,0:08:41.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- All right!\N - That's Ukyo-{\i1}sensei{\i0} for you!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.47,0:08:44.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Just when I was finally on stage...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.89,0:08:47.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In that case, Yuma-{\i1}kun{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.18,0:08:49.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,To summarize, you Duel with me!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.43,0:08:51.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sure! It'd be my pleasure!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.48,0:08:55.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Duel Disk, set!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.73,0:08:58.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,D-Gazer, set!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.94,0:09:01.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Duel Target: Lock-On!!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.28,0:09:07.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Link established between A and B.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.37,0:09:09.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Duel!!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.29,0:09:11.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You can do it, Yuma!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.25,0:09:15.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yuma-{\i1}kun{\i0}, is there any merit to the\N rumors that you defeated Shark?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.71,0:09:17.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You bet! It's true!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.71,0:09:19.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I just can't believe that.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.71,0:09:22.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That you did, despite having never defeated me in your entire life.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.17,0:09:24.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's the truth, Committee Chairman.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.38,0:09:26.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We're the witnesses!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.14,0:09:29.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So I see. Meaning that if I were to win this Duel...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.43,0:09:34.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,To summarize, it would mean that I am\N stronger than Shark, correct?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.10,0:09:36.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You keep saying "to summarize"...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.81,0:09:40.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It'd be really bad if your throat was\N {\i1}sum-mothered{\i0} by that sea lion-sized sentence!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.65,0:09:42.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"If my throat was smothered"?!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.32,0:09:45.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay, let's get it on!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.86,0:09:47.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I got me a Numbers card!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.41,0:09:48.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.87,0:09:51.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Gone! The Numbers' gone!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.87,0:09:52.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Here I come!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.66,0:09:54.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My turn! Draw!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.71,0:10:00.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,H-HOLD ON A MINUTE!!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.96,0:10:02.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Go, Bugman X!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.13,0:10:07.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Direct Attack!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.14,0:10:11.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You gotta be kidding!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.01,0:10:13.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,4,000 to zero...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.68,0:10:15.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Y-Yuma...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.35,0:10:17.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He totally wiped the floor with you!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.56,0:10:22.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,As expected, someone like Yuma-{\i1}kun{\i0} who never studies could never beat me!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.86,0:10:26.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,To summarize, a fool can't hope to win a Duel.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.40,0:10:27.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.74,0:10:29.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't be like that, now.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.12,0:10:32.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Life and Dueling are one and the same.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.33,0:10:34.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It never goes just as you plan.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.95,0:10:37.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,One should learn through messing up.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.25,0:10:42.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Bugman, for example, lives off of failure.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.97,0:10:47.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Bugman...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.13,0:10:50.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,An electrical fairy that lives off of the other bugs.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.14,0:10:53.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It becomes extremely powerful because it lives off its bug friends.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.60,0:10:58.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's said that those who witness its full moon like appearance may forever live in happiness.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.23,0:11:03.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sensei, to summarize, there's no such thing as stuff like that in real life!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.02,0:11:05.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There is. I'm sure of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.11,0:11:10.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yuma, it's fine that you lost just now.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.36,0:11:11.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You just have to learn from it.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.70,0:11:16.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Isn't that the challenge spirit you like to call "bringing it to 'em"?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.41,0:11:18.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ukyo-{\i1}sensei{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.37,0:11:19.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're right!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.71,0:11:21.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll always keep bringin' it to 'em!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.92,0:11:26.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ukyo-{\i1}sensei{\i0} sure is a nice guy!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.51,0:11:30.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He's really smart when it comes to teaching math and he's really nice on top of it!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.13,0:11:32.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm definitely gonna become like that man!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.14,0:11:39.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hi, Yuma!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.85,0:11:40.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sis!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.90,0:11:43.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why don't the two of you come for a little drive?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.77,0:11:50.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's a certainly a good thing that the computer virus incident that spread yesterday only lasted for a while.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.95,0:11:54.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But what if things had lasted much longer?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.62,0:11:59.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There's a very good chance the entire city would be thrown into a huge panic.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.58,0:12:02.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A-A huge panic?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.29,0:12:05.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Beyond traffic lights or vending machines.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.71,0:12:08.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Suppose the banks' data was erased and rewritten.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.67,0:12:12.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Or say the hospital lost all its data.\N It'd be a terrible thing, wouldn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.93,0:12:15.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Y-You serious?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.55,0:12:17.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Who would try to do such a thing?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.60,0:12:22.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, the computer virus was transferred from the jurisdiction within your school.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.31,0:12:28.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I want the two of you to stake out the jurisdiction.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.90,0:12:31.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There's a good chance the culprit will appear again.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.45,0:12:33.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This seems pretty interesting, don't you think?!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.45,0:12:35.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hold it. Why do we have to do this?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.66,0:12:37.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't wanna hear any complaints!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.53,0:12:39.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's {\i1}my{\i0} article that was ruined by this!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.33,0:12:44.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Once we find the culprit, I'll karate chop the guy 'till he's blue in the face!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.71,0:12:45.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Listen up, Yuma.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.88,0:12:51.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Your sister said the culprit is sure to appear in the library so he can access its personal computer.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.51,0:12:53.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What a drag...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.13,0:12:56.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Gosh! Shape up and get on look-out already!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.02,0:13:05.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's almost closing time.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.10,0:13:07.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe he's just not coming today?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.65,0:13:11.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yuma, look! Isn't that...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.07,0:13:13.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Committee Chairman!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.90,0:13:15.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He looks pretty suspicious...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.53,0:13:17.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yuma!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.08,0:13:22.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's a flash drive!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.96,0:13:30.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't tell me this is...!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.17,0:13:32.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Caught you!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.26,0:13:32.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wha-
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.46,0:13:35.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So you were the culprit behind that incident!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.68,0:13:36.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I am not!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.68,0:13:38.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I am not the culprit!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.18,0:13:39.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I was being used!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.47,0:13:41.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're a liar!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.18,0:13:43.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We just saw you input the virus!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.06,0:13:44.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What're you doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.23,0:13:46.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm intervening the culprit!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.52,0:13:50.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If I search for any locations that\N accessed this machine from the outside,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.32,0:13:52.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,the culprit has to be there!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.57,0:13:54.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Damn it!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.15,0:13:57.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I came here to retrieve the data files so I could reveal the culprit's whereabouts!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.53,0:14:02.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Without knowing it, I activated the installation files that launched the virus bomb!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.79,0:14:05.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I accidentally released the virus bomb into the city!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.58,0:14:07.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Found him!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.63,0:14:12.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He triggered the virus bomb?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.63,0:14:15.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Yeah! I'm looking for the culprit!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.01,0:14:17.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}So you have to do something about the bomb, Sis!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.05,0:14:21.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hold on, Yuma!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.68,0:14:24.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's over there!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.52,0:14:27.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The culprit is inside the nodule within the top of the tower!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.60,0:14:31.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You sure the culprit's really hiding out in here?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.19,0:14:33.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I am. He is here, without a doubt.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.86,0:14:36.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Surprise, surprise.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.65,0:14:39.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Despite the various options, you made it here so quickly.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.95,0:14:41.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ukyo-{\i1}sensei{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.45,0:14:43.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why are you here, Sensei?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.25,0:14:51.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So, to summarize, Ukyo-{\i1}sensei{\i0} is the culprit?!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.34,0:14:53.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I suppose you could say that.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.17,0:14:55.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You gotta be pulling my leg, Sensei!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.21,0:14:58.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The very fact that our Committee Chairman was able to make it here was all within my expectations.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.55,0:15:01.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,To summarize, this was a trap!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.76,0:15:06.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The virus bomb you uploaded will go off in a mere 30 minutes.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.73,0:15:12.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Because I truly wanted you to witness firsthand my virus bomb being set off.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.44,0:15:14.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So that makes me your accomplice?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.78,0:15:20.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Numbers!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.70,0:15:24.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Observation number four...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.24,0:15:26.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"This is not something of this world."
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.70,0:15:29.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It may be hiding some kind of message within it.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.46,0:15:31.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Like a puzzle of some sort.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.42,0:15:33.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What the?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.54,0:15:35.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Could that be a Numbers?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.55,0:15:41.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sensei...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.05,0:15:43.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's the mark of the Numbers...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.10,0:15:46.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You didn't get sent away?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.27,0:15:47.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Of course not.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.56,0:15:50.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But you weren't here all this time!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.48,0:15:51.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Y-Yuma-{\i1}kun{\i0}...?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.52,0:15:54.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why is he talking to himself?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.19,0:15:57.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe that Dueling Spirit appeared!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.11,0:16:00.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Talking with this guy's a waste of time!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.82,0:16:03.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sensei, why are you doing something so stupid?!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.57,0:16:06.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Consider this a challenge issued down from me!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.58,0:16:09.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It is no different from you "bringing it to 'em"!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.29,0:16:10.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No it's {\i1}not!!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.75,0:16:13.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Causing trouble for others isn't what we call "bringing it to 'em"!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.96,0:16:16.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yuma, let's Duel him.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.88,0:16:19.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,His heart is being engulfed by the Numbers.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.88,0:16:24.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Trying to persuade him is pointless unless we remove him from the Numbers.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.89,0:16:28.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's Duel, Sensei!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.43,0:16:31.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If you lose to me, you'll agree to stop that virus bomb!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.48,0:16:34.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Duel?!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.06,0:16:35.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So be it!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.27,0:16:37.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If you win, I'll stop the virus bomb!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.98,0:16:41.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But I do wonder if you can oppose me?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.49,0:16:44.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll show you my strength when I bring it to you!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.07,0:16:44.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's a match!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.87,0:16:48.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,D-Gazer, set!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.41,0:16:50.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Target: Lock-On!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.71,0:16:56.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Link established between A and B.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.17,0:16:58.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Duel!!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.92,0:17:01.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You can do it, Yuma!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.97,0:17:03.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You better win!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.43,0:17:06.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If you don't, I'll be framed as a criminal!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.18,0:17:08.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll be going first!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.22,0:17:10.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My turn! Draw!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.93,0:17:14.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I set a Monster in Face-Down Defense Position!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.15,0:17:17.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Face-Down Defense Position?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.48,0:17:20.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What kind of Monster did he set?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.48,0:17:23.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I will leave it at that and end my turn.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.24,0:17:25.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My turn!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.66,0:17:26.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Draw!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.36,0:17:28.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I Summon Gagaga Magician!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.54,0:17:38.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I have no idea what the Defense Power of the Monster he set is!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.38,0:17:41.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Fine! No use over thinking it!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.09,0:17:42.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Gagaga Magician!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.34,0:17:44.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Attack the thing!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.38,0:17:45.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Naive.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.89,0:17:50.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Come out, Bugman X!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.48,0:17:56.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's got 2000 Defense Points!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.52,0:18:00.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yuma's Monster stayed in one piece, but his Life fell!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.07,0:18:05.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When you attack a Monster with higher Defense Power, the attacking Monster isn't destroyed,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.53,0:18:07.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but its Attack Power is subtracted from the other's Defense Power.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.74,0:18:10.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,To summarize, that's 2000 - 1500!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.78,0:18:13.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,As a result, he takes 500 points of damage!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.41,0:18:15.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then it's my turn again!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.62,0:18:16.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Draw!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.17,0:18:19.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I Summon Bugman Y!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.13,0:18:25.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I continue with a Magic Card from my hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.05,0:18:26.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Bug Load activates!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.51,0:18:32.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This card lets both players select one Level Four or lower Monster on their field.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.76,0:18:38.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We can then Special Summon a Monster from our hands holding the same level as the chosen Monster.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.40,0:18:41.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I Special Summon Bugman Z!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.77,0:18:45.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay! I got a Monster in my hand\N with the same level as Gagaga Magician!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.49,0:18:48.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I have the Level Four Gogogo Golem!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.07,0:18:50.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm gonna take Gogogo Golem and-
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.12,0:18:52.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yuma, Summon it in Defense Position.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.83,0:18:57.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Gogogo Golem has an effect that will allow for it to not be destroyed in battle once per turn.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.04,0:19:01.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't mind Dueling, but I never asked\N for you to tell me how to Duel!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.00,0:19:05.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I Summon Gogogo Golem in Attack Mode!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.30,0:19:13.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How 'bout it?! You won't break 1800 Attack Points so easily!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.22,0:19:16.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You've just provided me with the chance\N I needed for my perfect victory!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.39,0:19:21.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I Overlay the Level Three Bugman X, Y and Z!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.07,0:19:28.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I construct the Overlay Network with my three Monsters!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.58,0:19:35.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He played it, as expected.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.29,0:19:38.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,An Exceeds Monster using three overlays?!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.29,0:19:39.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.37,0:19:40.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Exceeds Summon!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.83,0:19:41.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Show yourself!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.96,0:19:43.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Numbers 34!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.22,0:19:57.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Computer Beast Terabyte!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.06,0:20:01.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,N-Numbers?!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.85,0:20:04.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Please tell me what the Monster is!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.02,0:20:05.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A Numbers?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.36,0:20:10.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Got it!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.61,0:20:14.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wow, I got Revise Dragon in here now, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.57,0:20:18.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Huh? Did this guy take it or something?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.04,0:20:19.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Allow me to proceed!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.79,0:20:22.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I activate Terabyte's effect!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.33,0:20:26.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can use one of the Overlay Units on this card once per turn
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.84,0:20:31.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and gain control over one of the opponent's Level Four or lower Monsters for the turn!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.43,0:20:37.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is the perfection that makes up my Dueling!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.72,0:20:40.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ah! My Gogogo Golem is...!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.48,0:20:45.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Go, Gogogo Golem!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.57,0:20:53.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Gagaga!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.24,0:20:57.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I managed to access the program hosting the virus bomb...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.33,0:20:59.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But where is the activation switch?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.50,0:21:08.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So I have to search for it in this dungeon, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.04,0:21:10.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Under a time limit to boot...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.55,0:21:14.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What do you think of my perfect Dueling?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.55,0:21:16.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Perfect, perfect"...!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.93,0:21:18.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is perfection that important?!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.89,0:21:21.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It is. Perfection is everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.89,0:21:27.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I infected this city's program in order to seek the perfection I seek!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.44,0:21:29.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A dunce like you can't hope to win!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:30.98,0:21:32.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is the same Sensei I praised so much?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:32.94,0:21:34.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It hurts.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.70,0:21:36.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Where does it hurt?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.11,0:21:37.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My {\i1}heart!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:37.53,0:21:40.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Observation number five...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:40.03,0:21:42.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Humans feel pain in their hearts."
Dialogue: 0,0:21:42.12,0:21:43.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll be sure to remember that.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:43.50,0:21:49.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In summary, I understand this pain I'm feeling now all too well.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.04,0:21:49.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yuma-{\i1}kun{\i0}...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.71,0:21:50.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yuma-{\i1}kun{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:50.46,0:21:53.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I hate to bring it up at a time like this, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:53.84,0:21:58.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,, "To summarize" is meant to be the finalizing part of the sentence to give closure to the subject at hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:58.89,0:22:01.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So in the end, it gives off a meaning of "absolute finalization" of sorts...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:03.27,0:22:04.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Whac'cha talking about?!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:04.68,0:22:07.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can use it however I want!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:07.60,0:22:12.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}To summarize,{\i0} it means an idiot like yourself can't possibly hope to defeat me!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:24.00,0:22:25.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's start the Duel!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:27.08,0:22:28.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Here's this week's question!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:28.54,0:22:31.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Monster Cards have these star markings on them, you see?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:31.50,0:22:34.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And what exactly do these stars mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:40.32,0:22:44.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Today's test is hard. I can't divide myself from pleasure and temptation.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:44.93,0:22:49.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I wanna watch TV when I get home.\N The recent anime are fun.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:00.04,0:23:04.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}In any case, this test is hard. \NLanguage, Math and English are especially bad.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:04.54,0:23:09.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I'm only average at science and social studies.\N The only thing I'm good at is P.E.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:09.72,0:23:12.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}(Wait up, Baby!) For who's sake...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:12.42,0:23:14.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}(Is that, Baby!) ...am I remembering...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:14.86,0:23:17.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}(Just hold on, Baby!) ...the answer...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:17.42,0:23:18.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}(What are we!? Baby!) ...they wanted?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:19.09,0:23:23.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Even if I write the correct answer on this paper,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:23.83,0:23:28.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}in one year, in ten years, will anything change?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:28.57,0:23:33.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The world I drew in the corner of my dreams,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:33.67,0:23:38.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}one day I will race through the open sky.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:38.45,0:23:43.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}No one can blame this heart of mine.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:43.32,0:23:48.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Nothing is really correct!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:20.95,0:24:23.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You can't beat him in this Duel.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:23.20,0:24:25.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't wanna hear that from you!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:25.62,0:24:27.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hurry! We're almost out of time!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:27.49,0:24:29.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Next time on Yu-Gi-Oh! ZeXal!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:29.41,0:24:32.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"The Countdown to Reversal! The Ace-In-The-Hole's Astral!?"
Dialogue: 0,0:24:32.12,0:24:34.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm gonna bring it to 'em!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:36.04,0:24:38.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And the answer is...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:38.05,0:24:40.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's the Monster's level!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:40.09,0:24:44.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If it's got four stars, it means it's a "Level Four"!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:44.51,0:24:49.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You can bet a higher level Monster's gonna have a ton of 'em!
